<task id="AIRA-013" project="ai-spaarke-platform-enhancments-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Wire Reference Retrieval into RagService</title>
    <phase>2</phase>
    <estimate>3h</estimate>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-search</tags>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>D</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Extend RagService (or create ReferenceRetrievalService) with a `SearchReferencesAsync` method that queries the dedicated golden reference index.</goal>
    <context>
      The existing RagService queries spaarke-knowledge-index-v2 for customer document RAG. We need a parallel query path that targets spaarke-rag-references for golden reference knowledge. The playbook's N:N knowledge source relationships provide knowledgeSourceIds for filtering.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Must query spaarke-rag-references ONLY — never the customer document index
      - Support filtering by knowledgeSourceIds (from playbook N:N relationships)
      - Support filtering by domain tag
      - Must include tenantId filter on all queries (security)
      - Return format compatible with prompt assembly (content text + metadata)
      - Follow ADR-009 for Redis caching of results
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      .claude/adr/ADR-009-redis-caching.md
      .claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md
      .claude/patterns/caching/distributed-cache.md
      .claude/constraints/ai.md
      docs/guides/RAG-ARCHITECTURE.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step>Read `Services/Ai/RagService.cs` to understand existing query patterns and response types</step>
    <step>Add `SearchReferencesAsync` method to IRagService/RagService:
      - Parameters: query, knowledgeSourceIds?, domain?, topK=5, cancellationToken
      - Queries: spaarke-rag-references index only
      - Filters: tenantId (required) + knowledgeSourceIds (optional) + domain (optional)</step>
    <step>Create response model `ReferenceSearchResult` with: content, knowledgeSourceId, knowledgeSourceName, domain, score</step>
    <step>Implement hybrid search (keyword + vector + semantic reranking) against the reference index</step>
    <step>Add unit tests for SearchReferencesAsync</step>
    <step>Verify existing RagService methods are not affected (no regression)</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>Bash, Read, Write, Edit, Glob, Grep</tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>SearchReferencesAsync method on RagService (or new ReferenceRetrievalService)</output>
    <output>ReferenceSearchResult model</output>
    <output>Unit tests</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>SearchReferencesAsync queries spaarke-rag-references only</criterion>
    <criterion>Supports filtering by knowledgeSourceIds and domain</criterion>
    <criterion>tenantId filter always applied</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests pass</criterion>
    <criterion>Existing RagService methods unaffected</criterion>
    <criterion>dotnet build succeeds with 0 errors</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
